---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Evan's Drunken Holes | Saturday, July 17</title>
    <meta name="description" content="A field guide for an actually good Saturday bar night in the East Village and Lower East Side." />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Mono:wght@400;500&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-top"><span>JACK'S FIELD GUIDE</span><span>NYC / SATURDAY</span><span>17 JULY 2026</span></div>
        <p class="kicker">FOR EVAN, AND WHOEVER ELSE GETS THE TEXT</p>
        <h1>A good night<br /><i>without the</i> bullshit.</h1>
        <div class="hero-bottom">
          <p>Seven bars for a Saturday that begins casually, gets loose, and still has a chance of putting cool people in your path.</p>
          <a href="#plan">The night plan <span>↓</span></a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="manifesto" id="plan">
        <div class="number">00</div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">THE BRIEF</p>
          <h2>Drinks, no dinner. A lot of people. No recent-grad gauntlet.</h2>
          <p class="lede">This is a list for 25–32ish energy: places with friction, character, prices that do not induce early restraint, and enough room to meet people. The scoring favors a bar you can walk into without performing taste.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="criteria">
        <p class="eyebrow">HOW THE LIST WORKS</p>
        <div class="criteria-grid">
          <div><b>01</b><h3>Social gravity</h3><p>Is there an actual reason to talk to people, or just groups guarding their tables?</p></div>
          <div><b>02</b><h3>Price elasticity</h3><p>Can everyone buy another round without somebody announcing the Uber home at 11:15?</p></div>
          <div><b>03</b><h3>Crowd maturity</h3><p>The point is energy, not internship-summer chaos or after-work finance cosplay.</p></div>
          <div><b>04</b><h3>Saturday readiness</h3><p>A place must be alive enough to matter, but not so loud that the only plan is to get drunker.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="route">
        <p class="eyebrow">THE PLAN, IF WE WANT ONE</p>
        <div class="route-line"><span>9:30</span><strong>The Magician</strong><i>Get in before the room goes full.</i></div>
        <div class="route-line"><span>11:00</span><strong>Bua <em>or</em> The Lions</strong><i>Pick Bua for volume, Lions for a better-looking crowd.</i></div>
        <div class="route-line"><span>12:30</span><strong>Ace Bar</strong><i>Pool, pinball, dartboard. Let the night spill outward.</i></div>
        <div class="route-note">Alternate ending: 169 Bar, before midnight, if weird and cheap wins the vote.</div>
      </section>

      <section class="spots">
        <div class="spots-heading"><p class="eyebrow">THE OPTIONS</p><p>Tap a bar for directions or its current details.</p></div>
        {stops.map((stop) => (
          <article class="spot">
            <div class="spot-image">{stop.photos.map((photo) => <a href={stop.source} target="_blank" title={`Verified ${photo.label.toLowerCase()} photo source for ${stop.name}`}><img src={photo.src} alt={`${stop.name} ${photo.label.toLowerCase()} photo`} loading="lazy" /><span>{photo.label}</span></a>)}</div>
            <div class="spot-copy">
              <div class="spot-meta"><span>{stop.rank}</span><span>{stop.area}</span><span>FIT {stop.score}</span></div>
              <h2>{stop.name}</h2>
              <p class="moment">{stop.moment}</p>
              <p>{stop.note}</p>
              <p class="why">{stop.why}</p>
              <dl><div><dt>PRICE</dt><dd>{stop.price}</dd></div><div><dt>SOCIAL</dt><dd>{stop.social}</dd></div><div><dt>CROWD</dt><dd>{stop.crowd}</dd></div></dl>
              <div class="links"><a href={stop.maps} target="_blank">Map it ↗</a><a href={stop.site} target="_blank">Venue details ↗</a></div>
            </div>
          </article>
        ))}
      </section>

      <section class="atlas">
        <div class="atlas-heading">
          <div><p class="eyebrow">THE FULL FIELD ATLAS</p><h2>32 more doors, all worth knowing.</h2></div>
          <p>These are not all equal picks. They are the live alternatives: choose the room that matches the group, then commit before the first round turns into a committee meeting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="atlas-grid">
          {moreStops.map((stop, index) => (
            <article class="atlas-card">
              <a class="atlas-image" href={stop.source} target="_blank" title={`Wide venue photo source for ${stop.name}`}>
                <img src={stop.image} alt={`Wide view of ${stop.name}`} loading="lazy" />
                <span>VIEW {String(index + 8).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
              </a>
              <div class="atlas-copy">
                <div><span>{stop.area}</span><span>{stop.price}</span></div>
                <h3>{stop.name}</h3>
                <p class="atlas-fit">{stop.fit}</p>
                <p>{stop.note}</p>
                <a href={`https://maps.google.com/?q=${encodeURIComponent(`${stop.name} New York NY`)}`} target="_blank">Map it ↗</a>
              </div>
            </article>
